    "description": {
      "es": "",
      "en": "Constructs a ZoneInfo object from a file-like object returning bytes (e.g. a file opened in binary mode or an io.BytesIO object). Unlike the primary constructor, this always constructs a new object. The key parameter sets the name of the zone for the purposes of __str__() and __repr__(). Objects created via this constructor cannot be pickled (see pickling). ValueError is raised if the data read from file_obj is not a valid TZif file."
